Martha Tabram (née White; 10 May 1849 – 7 August 1888) was an English woman killed in a spate of violent murders in Whitechapel, in the East End of London. She may have been the first victim of the still-unidentified Jack the Ripper.
Although not one of the canonical five Ripper victims that historians have broadly acknowledged, she is considered the next most likely candidate.
